<br>
&quot;Scenario 1: Guild A kills, B now up. B, without passing, decides to let Guild Y try Mob 1. Guild Y goes in, kills. B is still up next. The Rotation is then A, Y, B, C, D.&quot;<br>
<br>
Now I never understand why B doesnt lose their turn by letting guild Y have a go. You could get the situation where guild B is letting numerious guilds have a go in order for guild C to not get a turn for a while..something like this...<br>
<br>
A...B (let Y)...Y (Win)....B (Let X)...X (fail)....B(let W)....W (Fail)...etc etc..  Making C have to wait along time.  <br>
<br>
btw this isnt any instance but its just something which COULD happen in theory.<br>
