<br>
Most times the 'stepping aside' has been done to avoid the messiness that has happened over and over. <br>
<br>
If Guild Z goes in to the Raid site, and Guild B does also, havoc ensues, flames erupt, and the RTA has a field day.<br>
<br>
Guild B, knowing that they will have their regularly scheduled turn, no matter the outcome of Guild Z's attempt, is more likely to be amenable.<br>
<br>
In theory, IF a guild was to constantly 'step aside' to let others in the Rotation, they would have to answer to the other guilds in that Rotation. <br>
<br>
And since the Rotations are there cause the folks on them really really want the loot, I can't see any guild doing the Scenario you describe. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ujlxaac.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jlxaac</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(8/13/02 3:18:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Question about Planes + 1</span><hr size=1> does the 2am rule exist only for planes?<br>
